title: TMO will want 890 eV to start (same photon energy as what they ended with)
TMO will want 890 eV to start (same photon energy as what they ended with)
Loading config from last night, but orbit has a lot of hysteresis effects; steering flat
Tuned up to 1 mj
text: Jitter is better too, used XCAV launch set points

title: CATER 154979, Kly Mod 21-4: frequent FLKs.
text: Kly Mod 21-4: station fault log shows a number of HVOV + several HVOC faults. Ranged thyratron from 4.4 to 4.9 volts to get better BV stability. Had station trip off due to HVOV fault while ranging thyratron. Lowered HV set from 22.65 KV to 22.3 KV to hopefully prevent more HVOV faults. BV now about 345.5 KV with 360 expected. Station FTPs + history plots look better. CATER ready to close.

title: CATER 154974, Kly Mod 27-7: station has excessive phase jitter.
text: Kly Mod 27-7: ranged thyratron from 4.12 to 4.6 volts. HL = 4.65 volts. Station more stable according to klystron history plots + FTPs.

title: * Re: 10-2 tripped on peak power - recovered fine -> again -> again -> again
Fill rate is dropping--going to TUNE mode...
FACET charge didn't recover after the most recent 10-2 trip
text: We didn't notice that the gun RF was off for a while this time so the structure had more time to cool than it did during previous trips. Each time we recover the gun the Schottky phase wanders for a while as the temperature stabilizes, but this time it seems like the phase isn't returning to its normal value.

title: MEC finished, switching over to our dual energy config for XPP / CXI /TMO
* Re: FACET charge didn't recover - never mind, it just recovered
text: Below see plot of QE over the last two hours. I'm guessing that the gun cooled off enough that when we did turn it on again there was a period of time when the water cooling was chasing the temperature too aggressively and causing an oscillation around the correct temperature (and phase). I guess that resolved itself just after I made my alarmed elog entry.
